The paper proposes a deep learning model for question answering, which falls under the natural language processing (NLP) domain. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The model also involves iterative decoding, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (AI) research, making cs.AI a likely sub-category as well. The model also involves fusion of representations, which is a common technique in machine learning (ML) research, making cs.LG a possible sub-category. The model also involves information retrieval (IR) techniques such as coattention, making cs.IR a possible sub-category. Finally, the model involves dynamic pointing, which is a technique commonly used in neural networks (NN) research, making cs.NE a possible sub-category.
